From 7a9037a41a832ec8397f54b2af5cb7fa17d55aa1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Geoff <geoff.radian6@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 2026 22:13:33 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat: implement full Phase 1 alpha for ComputeClass-aware
 provisioning
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

This completes all P0 requirements from the PRD:

R4: NAP conflict detection
- NAPDetector queries GKE cluster autoscaling config at startup
- Warns if NAP is enabled; optionally fails with --strict-nap-check
- Exposed GKEClient on Operator struct for main.go access

R5: Alpha feature gate
- --enable-computeclass flag (default: false) / ENABLE_COMPUTECLASS env var
- --strict-nap-check flag / STRICT_NAP_CHECK env var
- ComputeClass provider only wired up when feature gate is enabled

R6: Enhanced decision logging
- Kubernetes events for ComputeClass resolution (success and not-found)
- Structured log entries with priority match counts and fallback stats

R7: Backward compatibility
- main.go uses functional options pattern — no args change when CC disabled
- Existing deployments work identically without any config changes

Additional:
- DeepCopy methods for ComputeClassRef, ComputeClassPriorityRule, ComputeClassSpec
- Updated zz_generated.deepcopy.go for ComputeClassRef in GCENodeClassSpec
- ComputeClassDrift detection: triggers node replacement when CC ref changes
- Unit tests for drift detection (5 cases) and NAP detector
- Kubernetes event definitions for CC resolution lifecycle

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
